<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911014-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>911014-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Lep Group PLC:   Financing Pact Is Reached   With Firm's Principal Banks</HL><DATE>10/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LEPGY</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>INDUSTRIAL andamp; COMMERCIAL SERVICES, LEASING, CLEANING (ICS)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Lep Group PLC said in Greenwich, Conn., that it reachedagreement with its principal banks to continue their existingfinancing and offer an additional #40 million ($69 million)of credit.   The British freight transportation company, which made theannouncement through U.S. unit National Guardian Corp., saidNational Westminster Bank acted as the lead bank for morethan 30 banks. A spokesman didn't indicate the amount of thecurrent bank financing.</LP><TEXT>   Lep said the bank refinancing agreement will allow it to&quot;concentrate more fully&quot; on its previously announced plan tosell National Guardian, a provider of security and protectionservices, and continue with the development of its coretransportation business.</TEXT></DOC>